Claude Connectors for Creative Software: Anthropic launches direct integrations for Blender, Autodesk Fusion, Adobe Creative Cloud (50+ tools), Ableton, Splice, SketchUp, Affinity by Canva, and Resolume Arena .

74
00:09:30,625 --> 00:09:38,487
Claude can act as an on-demand tutor for complex software, write scripts, automate batch tasks, and translate formats.

75
00:09:38,487 --> 00:09:43,562
Educational partnerships with RISD, Ringling College, and Goldsmiths .

76
00:09:43,562 --> 00:09:44,687
Tool of the Week.

77
00:09:44,687 --> 00:09:50,100
Stripe Link for AI Agents  – Payment infrastructure for the agentic commerce era

78
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:58,875
Stripe has opened its Link wallet to autonomous AI agents: agents can process purchases, bookings, and tickets on behalf of users .

79
00:09:58,875 --> 00:10:08,525
The permission model is well-designed – users authorize the agent via OAuth, the agent creates a purchase request, the user approves before payment.

80
00:10:08,525 --> 00:10:17,300
Agents never see raw payment data; instead, virtual cards with real-time authorization via "Issuing for agents" are provided .

81
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:24,937
For developers who want to equip agents with real purchasing capabilities, this is the most serious infrastructure solution to date.

82
00:10:24,937 --> 00:10:33,150
90-day purchase protection with select merchants, configurable spending limits coming in the future, and stablecoin support in development .

83
00:10:33,150 --> 00:10:39,300
Stripe is positioning itself as the payment rail for the agentic economy, before demand explodes.

84
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:52,075
Particularly relevant for teams building booking, shopping, or service agents: Stripe Link solves the "who pays and how?" problem with a framework that already accounts for users, liability, and compliance.

85
00:10:52,075 --> 00:10:53,225
Fail of the Week.

86
00:10:53,225 --> 00:10:59,512
Sam Altman Criticizes Anthropic's Cyber Restrictions – Then Introduces Exactly the Same Thing.

87
00:10:59,512 --> 00:11:16,762
A few weeks after Sam Altman called Anthropic's decision not to publicly release its cybersecurity model Mythos "fear-based marketing," OpenAI introduced exactly the same model for GPT-5.5: restricted access via "Trusted Access for Cyber (TAC)" .

88
00:11:16,762 --> 00:11:27,312
Users must submit credentials and intended use before gaining access to penetration testing, vulnerability exploitation, and malware reverse engineering features.

89
00:11:27,312 --> 00:11:32,762
OpenAI is working with the US government to identify legitimate cyber defenders .

90
00:11:32,762 --> 00:11:42,850
The wording of Altman's original criticism of Anthropic – "fear-based marketing" – now hangs in the air while OpenAI applies the same decision logic he had criticized.

91
00:11:42,850 --> 00:11:46,900
Anthropic has surely noticed the screenshot potential of this moment.

92
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:58,075
What we learn: Once a company understands what powerful cybersecurity models can actually do, everyone reaches the same conclusion – no matter how loudly they previously said the opposite.

93
00:11:58,075 --> 00:12:00,750
The restriction is substantively justified.

94
00:12:00,750 --> 00:12:03,400
The communication strategy before it was not.

